#: DT_Tutorials export[0] offset=0x33df
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=379
msgctxt "DT_Tutorials@e0@33df"
msgid "To remove a module link, enter <Bold>Link mode</> with <Bold>F</> or the toolbar, select a module that you have previously linked, and then select the destination module you want to unlink from it.\r\n\r\nHold <Bold>Shift</> to quickly un-link a module from multiple destinations.\r\n\r\nYou can also <Bold>remove all links</> by selecting a module in Link mode and pressing <Bold>X</>."
msgstr ""

#: DT_Tutorials export[0] offset=0x35ac
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=23
msgctxt "DT_Tutorials@e0@35ac"
msgid "Advanced: Item Filters"
msgstr ""

#: DT_Tutorials export[0] offset=0x35f6
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=402
msgctxt "DT_Tutorials@e0@35f6"
msgid "If you want more control over exactly what will be sent to Storage Units or Factories, you can use the <Bold>Item Filters</> panel.\r\n\r\nFrom here you can highlight any inventory slot and choose which items can be stored there, set a maximum limit for that item, or completely disable the slot.\r\n\r\nThere are also several functions for copying the current slot to all others, or from one slot to another."
msgstr ""

#: DT_Tutorials export[0] offset=0x37da
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=26
msgctxt "DT_Tutorials@e0@37da"
msgid "Advanced: Extra Functions"
msgstr ""

#: DT_Tutorials export[0] offset=0x3827
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=483
msgctxt "DT_Tutorials@e0@3827"
msgid "Clicking the <Bold>cog</> button opens the <Bold>Advanced Settings</> panel.\r\n\r\nFrom here you can <Bold>label</> any module with a custom tag which appears in the <Bold>Status View</> as well as several other functions.\r\n\r\nYou can also choose a module's <Bold>priority</> in this panel. Modules with a higher priority will <Bold>take more resources</> from sources than those with a lower priority - which is extremely useful for streamlining your station's manufacturing processes."
msgstr ""

#: DT_Tutorials export[0] offset=0x3a5c
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=20
msgctxt "DT_Tutorials@e0@3a5c"
msgid "Onboarding Complete"
msgstr ""

#: DT_Tutorials export[0] offset=0x3aa3
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=283
msgctxt "DT_Tutorials@e0@3aa3"
msgid "Congratulations Station Commander, you've completed the <Bold>Nova Corp Onboarding Process</>.\r\n\r\nYou're now ready to go forth and <Bold>build, explore and expand</> your industrial empire across the TAU system.\r\n\r\nWe see great things in your future, Commander - <Bold>good luck!</>"
msgstr ""

#: DT_Tutorials export[0] offset=0x3c10
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=21
msgctxt "DT_Tutorials@e0@3c10"
msgid "Particle Accelerator"
msgstr ""

#: DT_Tutorials export[0] offset=0x3c58
#. encoding=ASCII len_field=506
msgctxt "DT_Tutorials@e0@3c58"
msgid "To generate <Bold>Antimatter</> you must construct a <Bold>Particle Accelerator Loop</>.\r\n\r\nThis is constructed from a <Bold>Control Station</>, one or more <Bold>Towers</>, all connected together via <Bold>Conduit</>.\r\n\r\nOnce you have a complete loop and have supplied your station with the required input items, you can start generating antimatter.\r\n\r\nThe <Bold>longer</> the loop you construct, the <Bold>faster</> you can generate antimatter, but the <Bold>more power</> your accelerator will require."
msgstr ""

